1
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:19,000
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
<i>[Episode 40]</i>

3
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:29,500
My friend introduced me to a businessman

4
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,000
who works with handicraft exports.

5
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,000
I have an appointment with him tomorrow in the afternoon.

6
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,100
After we send the stuff back in the morning, you can come with me for the meeting.

7
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,900
There's no need for that. Let's split up for the day.

8
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:42,200
A colleague of my friend is working as a travel consultant.

9
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,800
He can advise me on useful resources.

10
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,200
Okay.

11
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,200
What's wrong?

12
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:56,600
What's on your mind when you're looking at this clock?

13
00:01:58,100 --> 00:02:00,100
Time.

14
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:03,200
I always feel that it's the embodiment of our hotel.

15
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:06,200
I'm just a gear in it.

16
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,600
Every part of this time device is working together

17
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,600
to maintain the clock's precision.

18
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,300
Beautiful, isn't it?

19
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:18,200
I can only see time.

20
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:21,600
That's because you're a customer.

21
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,000
You, too, are a customer now.

22
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,100
I am.

23
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:30,800
- Hongdou!
- Manager Liu!

24
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:32,600
- It's been a long time.
- I haven't seen you in a while.

25
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:35,400
I heard you came back, but I didn't manage to catch you.

26
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:40,100
- Who's this?
- This is my boyfriend.

27
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:42,900
He's my former colleague from the Housekeeping Department, Manager Liu.

28
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:45,100
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

29
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:48,700
I'd better let you go. I still have other tasks to attend to.

30
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,400
If you need anything, come looking for me.

31
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,700
- Sure, see you.
- See you.

32
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,000
Why did he call your name straight up?

33
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,600
He used to like me.

34
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,000
Really?

35
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,200
I'm not down for office romance.

36
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,100
You have so many rules!

37
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,600
Why are there flowers here?

38
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,600
Is this part of the service?

39
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,700
Manager Xu, you're always welcome to come home.

40
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:31,900
Wish you and Mr. Xie a blissful and fulfilling life.

41
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,400
Nice, isn't it?

42
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,600
- Take your time.
- Okay.

43
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,500
Let me show you around.

44
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:49,100
The kitchen and the dining room are on the first floor,

45
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:51,400
as well as all the lounges. The tea room there is included.

46
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,700
All these are for common use.

47
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,400
However, you must clean up

48
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,600
after you use the areas.

49
00:03:57,600 --> 00:04:00,200
The housekeeper is only responsible

50
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:03,100
for cleaning public areas.

51
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,400
Here, your room is on the second floor.

52
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,700
Be careful when you come up the stairs.

53
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,200
Okay.

54
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,200
Be careful.

55
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,800
This room over here.

56
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,000
Mr. Hu!

57
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:27,000
- Let me introduce some new neighbors. Miao Miao and Xiao Gang.
- This is Mr. Hu.

58
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,200
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you, Mr. Hu.

59
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,800
Come on in.

60
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,900
Welcome.

61
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,000
Take a look around.

62
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,600
<i>- What do you think?
- Excellent.</i>

63
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,660
<i>If you have any problems, just let me know.</i>

64
00:04:43,660 --> 00:04:45,300
<i>Okay.</i>

65
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:49,620
<i>[The path to freedom]</i>

66
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:34,400
<i>They need to be in the sun.</i>

67
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,500
<i>Only then can the leaves grow</i>

68
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:38,800
<i>with a lush green shade.</i>

69
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,200
<i>This is the process of photosynthesis.</i>

70
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,600
<i>Got it?</i>

71
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,400
What's the matter?

72
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,300
- I don't feel good.
- What's ailing you?

73
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,100
My heart is ailing me.

74
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,900
Your heart?

75
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,600
You drink, smoke, and stay up late all day long.

76
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,800
You had that coming.

77
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,800
Old Hu, I don't want to chide you.

78
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:14,600
We live together and take care of each other,

79
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,600
but we can't always be there for you.

80
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:19,400
No matter who is sick,

81
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,900
we can go to the hospital and take care of them for a few days.

82
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:25,300
However, if you're seriously ill, your parents are the ones shouldering the burden.

83
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:27,170
Is that what you want?

84
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,600
Stop shaking your head.

85
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,000
What in the world is wrong with your heart?

86
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,900
Should I take you to the hospital?

87
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,200
Xiaochun...

88
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,500
I want to go to Beijing.

89
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:46,400
Go on.

90
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,800
What now?

91
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:52,900
You want me to lend you some money to buy a ticket?

92
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,600
Aren't you going to ask me why I want to go there?

93
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,500
Nope, I'm not asking.

94
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:03,200
I'm not your dad, nor am I your mom.

95
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,600
You have no sense of humanity.

96
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,600
Aren't we friends?

97
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,300
The dog always chases its food.

98
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:12,200
I can read your mind.

99
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,300
Who are you calling a dog?

100
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:15,500
Who? You're the dog.

101
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:17,900
- You...
- A bastard.

102
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,000
All right.

103
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,600
Make a trip if you want to.

104
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,600
Sister Manjun is much older than you,

105
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,500
but she still has the courage to start over.

106
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,500
You're so young. Work hard.

107
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,800
I'm sure there'll be opportunities for you,

108
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,700
but I need to caution you.

109
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:36,200
The cost of living in big cities is extremely high.

110
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:39,100
Your life will be tough if you keep muddling along like this.

111
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,700
Got it?

112
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,000
You also need to know this.

113
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,800
Even if you're there,

114
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,800
you shouldn't get your hopes up.

115
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:50,400
You should let nature take its course when it comes to love.

116
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,700
All right! It's settled then.

117
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:58,100
If you don't renew your lease, your lease will only last until the end of this month.

118
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,600
I'll put up an advertisement for rental ten days in advance.

119
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,800
H-Hey... I haven't made my decision.

120
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,900
Spend a few more days contemplating. That's no problem.

121
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:07,200
Anyway, if you check out on short notice,

122
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:09,800
I won't refund the deposit.

123
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:14,100
You're such a heartless woman.

124
00:08:14,100 --> 00:08:16,200
Am I heartless?

125
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:22,300
<i>[The path to freedom]</i>

126
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,000
My girl is so pretty.

127
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,800
I'll tie a pretty braid for you.

128
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,000
Mom!

129
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:34,100
What brings you here today?

130
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:37,000
He picked me up today.

131
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,500
I was delivering goods to customers close by,

132
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,600
so I stopped by to see Xiao Hu Lu.

133
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,100
I called your mom,

134
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,400
and she asked me to pick her up.

135
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:48,000
I'll sleep in the homestay in town tonight.

136
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,000
I'll start cooking.

137
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,500
There aren't many ingredients at home, so it'll be a simple meal.

138
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,000
I won't eat here. I'll be off soon.

139
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,800
What's with you? Xiao Hu Lu missed you.

140
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,500
Leave after the meal.

141
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,400
Fine.

142
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,600
Let me help you with cooking.

143
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,200
Sure.

144
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:25,200
Luo Quan, your mom called me and told me your dad

145
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,200
was pretty harsh with the beating.

146
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,800
Are you okay now?

147
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,800
I'm fine now.

148
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,100
I heard that you went on a blind date recently.

149
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,800
How's the girl?

150
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,500
We've known each other for years,

151
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,600
so you should know me quite well.

152
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:51,600
I have a short fuse.

153
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,400
Sometimes, I talk without thinking

154
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,800
and my words are harsh.

155
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,400
I also have personality flaws.

156
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:00,600
So, our divorce isn't entirely your fault.

157
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,000
I have many issues as well.

158
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:08,900
One more thing. Don't take anything I said to you to heart.

159
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:11,400
In fact, I'm well aware

160
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:14,200
that you aren't a person who is lazy.

161
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:18,000
I know that you drank with customers

162
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:23,100
to sell water purifiers just to earn more money for the family.

163
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,000
I was too young.

164
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,000
After we had a child,

165
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,800
I felt that our life was a mess.

166
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:34,500
At that time, we weren't mature enough when dealing with problems.

167
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:38,700
We had a narrow perspective on things and were inexperienced.

168
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:42,100
As a result, our emotions overwhelmed us.

169
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:43,500
That's not true, Xiaochun.

170
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,600
It was my fault.

171
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:51,000
When we got married, I made a promise to you.

172
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,700
I would give you happiness.

173
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,000
But...

174
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:59,100
We were just too young.

175
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:02,300
We can't expect happiness from someone else.

176
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:09,540
Anyway, I've always felt that I let you down.

177
00:11:09,540 --> 00:11:12,070
Don't say that, Luo Quan.

178
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:15,560
I never regretted marrying you,

179
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:18,180
and I never regretted giving birth to Xiao Hu Lu.

180
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:19,660
Although we aren't a couple anymore,

181
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:22,570
I think we're living our respective lives well.

182
00:11:22,570 --> 00:11:24,039
You need to stop apologizing.

183
00:11:24,039 --> 00:11:29,049
We should let go of the past and look ahead. Okay?

184
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:38,240
Peel the beans.

185
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:51,000
Fry this one first. After that, add this in.

186
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,680
Got it. You need to turn it over slightly.

187
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:57,410
Gently. Yes, be gentle.

188
00:11:58,410 --> 00:12:00,700
- Welcome back!
- We're back!

189
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,520
What are you cooking? It smells delicious.

190
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,000
We're frying fish!

191
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,780
Frying little fishes, like me.

192
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:08,420
Aunty A'Gui is making something tasty. We've all eaten.

193
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:10,650
- Put your luggage away and come down for food!
- Sure.

194
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:11,979
- Okay.
- We'll get the luggage upstairs first.

195
00:12:11,979 --> 00:12:12,770
Okay.

196
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:16,200
Na Na, flip it over! It's going to burn!

197
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:27,420
Aunty A'Gui, your food is good enough to be served in a restaurant.

198
00:12:27,420 --> 00:12:30,800
A restaurant? I'm not good enough for that.

199
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:34,149
I'm just cooking with whatever ingredients are available. Right, Na Na?

200
00:12:34,149 --> 00:12:35,740
- Yes.
- Don't be too humble.

201
00:12:35,740 --> 00:12:38,120
Aunty Hua said that if you set up a restaurant,

202
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,360
Galsang Flower Restaurant will be out of business.

203
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,869
What a glib tongue! Showering me with all that flattery!

204
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:48,250
By the way, Mr. Hu is going to Beijing.

205
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:50,200
Going to Beijing?

206
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:54,060
Xiao Hu is going to Beijing to pursue love!

207
00:12:54,060 --> 00:12:55,690
Don't say that!

208
00:12:55,690 --> 00:12:57,409
I'm going to look for a job.

209
00:12:57,409 --> 00:13:01,690
What's so embarrassing about pursuing love? Right?

210
00:13:01,690 --> 00:13:04,730
Exactly! A goal is always good.

211
00:13:04,730 --> 00:13:06,259
What about your job?

212
00:13:06,259 --> 00:13:07,620
I haven't found one yet.

213
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:11,270
I plan to apply for a job in the production department of a music company.

214
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:14,240
I still want to work with music. Perhaps I'll be able to release an album.

215
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,800
That'd be amazing!

216
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:18,230
You should've done so eons ago. What a lazy bum.

217
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:19,520
Screw you!

218
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:22,700
Eons ago, I was just a bug in a stone crack.

219
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:24,550
There's a fabulous saying.

220
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:27,730
The best time to plant a tree is 10 years ago.

221
00:13:27,730 --> 00:13:31,180
The next best time is now.

222
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:34,000
You shouldn't be called Hu Youyu.

223
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
You should be called Hu Youli.
<i>("Youli" meaning "finding excuses")</i>

224
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,410
In my opinion, Hu Youli is a nice name.

225
00:13:38,410 --> 00:13:41,650
I'll consider changing my name.

226
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:47,240
By the way, today is my last day performing at the bar.

227
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,420
I'd like to invite everyone over to enjoy my last show together.

228
00:13:49,420 --> 00:13:51,650
- What do you think?
- No problem.

229
00:13:51,650 --> 00:13:53,590
Chairman Xie and I can't go.

230
00:13:53,590 --> 00:13:56,600
A horse is giving birth at the horse ranch today. We need to head there.

231
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,600
What? You need to accompany a horse for its delivery?

232
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,889
Not exactly. The foal is in an abnormal fetal position. That's why I'm worried.

233
00:14:01,889 --> 00:14:04,540
Aunty A'Gui hasn't been to a bar. Go and feel the vibes.

234
00:14:04,540 --> 00:14:07,290
No, I can't go. People like us aren't suitable for such a place.

235
00:14:07,290 --> 00:14:09,500
It's filled with loonies dancing and shouting wildly.

236
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,820
I'm not going.

237
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:12,820
- There aren't any loonies.
- I'm not going.

238
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:16,140
Aunty A'Gui, Mr. Hu works at a bar that serves non-alcoholic drinks.

239
00:14:16,140 --> 00:14:17,140
It's not noisy there.

240
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:18,870
I won't go no matter what.

241
00:14:18,870 --> 00:14:20,730
You've never been there. Let's go together.

242
00:14:20,730 --> 00:14:23,340
Nope. I'm going to bed at 9:00.

243
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:24,999
You should take on new challenges!

244
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,160
Just grab a drink and come back. It won't take up much of your time.

245
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:30,340
No, I'm not going.

246
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:52,100
♪ <i>The rain falls through the window</i> ♪

247
00:14:52,100 --> 00:15:00,500
♪ <i>My heart dampens with the wafting mist</i> ♪

248
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:06,720
♪ <i>Tell me how to be better at hiding this</i> ♪

249
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:11,980
♪ <i>But the only answer is the falling rain</i> ♪

250
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:22,980
♪ <i>In this gloomy world, I slowly wipe clean</i> ♪

251
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:25,440
It's so rude of people to come here

252
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:28,690
to drink and chat

253
00:15:28,690 --> 00:15:31,020
without watching the performance.

254
00:15:31,020 --> 00:15:34,140
Let others do whatever they want.

255
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:37,000
This isn't a concert.

256
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,290
In the olden days, even when girls sang,

257
00:15:39,290 --> 00:15:41,100
the audience would clap for her.

258
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:43,170
Stop talking about the old days.

259
00:15:43,170 --> 00:15:45,320
Yeah.

